===institution:HIST 2112
===date:Wed Sep  3  8:36:16 2003
===more:Today, less than 15% of Americans belong to a union. Historically, Americans have been anti-union, viewing unions as "un-American." Why are so many Americans opposed to unions? Why were Berkman and Goldman seen as "radicals"? What did the Homestead strike of 1892 accomplish, if anything?
